{
  "doc_id": "7330",
  "text": "2 There is, however, evidence that mode of onset may be a related factor of importance, those with a more rapid onset and shorter DUP having a better outcome. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The chronicity of the behavioural disturbance evident within the Northwick Park sample prior to admission was often a striking feature of third-party accounts [CITATION_3] as were the high thresholds of tolerance that developed, notwithstanding the distress engendered. Such chronicity is characteristic of insidious onset and compatible with an impaired level of social and interpersonal relationships.",
